<HEADLINE>
NCC RULES CHUNGHWA TELECOM MUST CUT ADSL RATES BY 5.4 PERCENT
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Taipei,  April 27 (CNA) 04/27/07  19:51:52 (By Elizabeth Hsu)
</P>
<P>
The National Communications Commission (NCC) ruled Friday that
the partially state-owned Chunghwa Telecom Corp.  must cut its
monthly charges by 5.4 percent for data transmission services
through asymmetric digital subscriber lines (ADSL).
</P>
<P>
NCC officials said at least 3.7 million ADSL users will benefit
from the rate cut, enactment of which will date from April 1. The
officials anticipated that the drop will boost the popularity of
broadband online services.
</P>
<P>
The cut will mean that the 256K/64K monthly charge will drop from
NT$200 to NT$180, while 1M/64K will drop from NT$410 to NT$388,
2M/256K will fall from NT$440 to NT$416 and 8M/640K will drop
from NT$650 to NT$615.
</P>
